            "answer_text": "It comes from cards, apparently specifically from the game of whist, a precursor to bridge. It refers to a suit (spades, clubs, hearts, diamonds) in which one has many and/or high cards, and thus can expect to take many tricks when that suit is led. By extension, something one is good at, one\u2019s field of expertise, one\u2019s forte . ",
